collaborative filtering model using KNNWithMeans item_based¶

In [31]:
from surprise import KNNWithMeans
from surprise import Dataset
from surprise import accuracy
from surprise.model_selection import train_test_split
from surprise import Reader

df_co = Dataset.load_from_df(df_fifty[['author','product','score']], Reader(rating_scale=(1, 10)))
trainset, testset = train_test_split(df_co, test_size=.20,random_state=612)
In [32]:
algo = KNNWithMeans(k=50, sim_options={'name': 'pearson_baseline', 'user_based': False})
algo.fit(trainset)

Estimating biases using als...
Computing the pearson_baseline similarity matrix...
Done computing similarity matrix.
Out[32]:
<surprise.prediction_algorithms.knns.KNNWithMeans at 0x2279a189af0>
In [34]:
test_pred = algo.test(testset)
In [35]:
# get RMSE
print("Item-based Model : Test Set")
accuracy.rmse(test_pred, verbose=True)

RMSE: 2.6827

a collaborative filtering model using SVD¶

In [41]:
from surprise import SVD
from surprise.model_selection import cross_validate

svd = SVD(random_state=612)
svd.fit(trainset)
svd_pred = svd.test(testset)
In [42]:

Try and recommend top 5 products for test users¶

In [54]:
from collections import defaultdict

top_n = defaultdict(list)
for uid, iid, true_r, est, _ in test_pred:
    top_n[uid].append((iid, est))

for uid, user_ratings in top_n.items():
    user_ratings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
    top_n[uid] = user_ratings[:5]

In what business scenario you should use popularity based Recommendation Systems ?¶

  1. In the condition of cold start.
  2. We can use popularity based Recommendation Systems for trends.

In what business scenario you should use CF based Recommendation Systems¶

  1. By using CF based Recommendation Systems, personalised recommendation can be given to the user.
  2. Collaborative filtering can help recommenders to not overspecialize in a users profile.

What other possible methods can you think of which can further improve the recommendation for different users ?¶

By leveraging tools like Event Stream Processing and Intelligent Decisioning, and operationalize the entire recommendation process.

In [ ]:
